Have code that updates the configuration with a complex (object) value like so (where `value = {foo:["bar"]}`) and see that the resulting files puts everything on one line

```
configurationEditService.writeConfiguration(target, {
                    key: 'editor.formatter',
                    value
                });
```

- VSCode Version: 1.5.3
- OS Version: Win10

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Configuration: "typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterOpeningAndBeforeClosingNonemptyParenthesis": true
2. Format this code:

```
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
    selector: 'x-com',
    templateUrl: './app/x-com.html',
    providers: [XComSer]
})
export class XComponent {
}
```
1. There is no space before the closing parenthesis just before the export class XComponent line

- VSCode Version: 1.6.0-Insiders
- OS Version: OSX

Once we run below code, Relative Line Number no longer works.

```
      const options = vscode.window.activeTextEditor.options;
      options.cursorStyle = vscode.TextEditorCursorStyle.Block;
      vscode.window.activeTextEditor.options = options;
```
## Update

Even if you set `lineNumbers` as `relative` in settings.json, `vscode.window.activeTextEditor.options.lineNumbers` is still `1` instead of `2`, which leads to this bug.
